#: ../../source/faq.rst:2
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:4
msgid ""
"Below are some frequently asked questions in three areas, with associated"
" answers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:8
msgid "OpenModelica General"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:11
msgid "Q: OpenModelica does not read the MODELICAPATH environment variable,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:11
msgid "even though this is part of the Modelica Language Specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:18
msgid "A: Use the OPENMODELICALIBRARY environment variable instead. We have"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:14
msgid ""
"temporarily switched to this variable, in order not to interfere with "
"other Modelica tools which might be installed on the same system. In the "
"future, we might switch to a solution with a settings file, that also "
"allows the user to turn on the MODELICAPATH functionality if desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:21
msgid "Q: How do I enter multi-line models into OMShell since it evaluates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:21
msgid "when typing the Enter/Return key?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:29
msgid "A: There are basically three methods: 1) load the model from a file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:24
msgid ""
"using the pull-down menu or the loadModel command. 2) Enter the "
"model/function as one (possibly long) line. 3) Type in the model in "
"another editor, where using multiple lines is no problem, and copy/paste "
"the model into OMShell as one operation, then push Enter. Another option "
"is to use OMNotebook instead to enter and evaluate models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:32
msgid "OMNotebook"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:34
msgid "Q: OMNotebook hangs, what to do?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:40
msgid "A: It is probably waiting for the omc.exe (compiler) process. (Under"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:37
msgid ""
"windows): Kill the processes omc.exe, g++.exe (C-compiler), as.exe "
"(assembler), if present. If OMNotebook then asks whether to restart OMC, "
"answer yes. If not, kill the process OMNotebook.exe and restart manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:43
msgid "Q: After a previous session, when starting OMNotebook again, I get a"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:43
msgid "strange message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:47
msgid "A: You probably quit the previous OpenModelica session in the wrong"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:46
msgid ""
"way, which left the process omc.exe running. Kill that process, and try "
"starting OMNotebook again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:51
msgid "Q: I copy and paste a graphic figure from Word or some other"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:50
msgid ""
"application into OMNotebook, but the graphic does not appear. What is "
"wrong?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:58
msgid "A: OMNotebook supports the graphic picture formats supported by Qt 4,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:54
msgid ""
"including the .png, .bmp (bitmap) formats, but not for example the gif "
"format. Try to convert your picture into one of the supported formats, "
"(e.g. in Word, first do paste as bitmap format), and then copy the "
"converted version into a text cell in OMNotebook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:63
msgid "Q: I select a cell, copy it (e.g. Ctrl-C), and try to paste it at"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:61
msgid ""
"another place in the notebook. However, this does not work. Instead some "
"other text that I earlier put on the clipboard is pasted into the nearest"
" text cell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:72
msgid "A: The problem is wrong choice of cursor mode, which can be text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:66
msgid ""
"insertion or cell insertion. If you click inside a cell, the cursor "
"become vertical, and OMNotebook expects you to paste text inside the "
"cell. To paste a cell, you must be in cell insertion mode, i.e., click "
"between two cells (or after a cell), you will get a vertical line. Place "
"the cursor carefully on that vertical line until you see a small "
"horizontal cursor. Then you should past the cell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:75
msgid "Q: I am trying to click in cells to place the vertical character"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:75
msgid "cursor, but it does not seem to react."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:81
msgid "A: This seems to be a Qt feature. You have probably made a selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:78
msgid ""
"(e.g. for copying) in the output section of an evaluation cell. This "
"seems to block cursor position. Click again in the output section to "
"disable the selection. After that it will work normally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:85
msgid "Q: I have copied a text cell and start writing at the beginning of"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:84
msgid ""
"the cell. Strangely enough, the font becomes much smaller than it should "
"be."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:90
msgid "A: This seems to be a Qt feature. Keep some of the old text and start"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:88
msgid ""
"writing the new stuff inside the text, i.e., at least one character "
"position to the right. Afterwards, delete the old text at the beginning "
"of the cell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:93
msgid "OMDev - OpenModelica Development Environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:96
msgid "Q: I get problems compiling and linking some files when using OMDev"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:96
msgid "with the MINGW (Gnu) C compiler under Windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:101
msgid "A: You probably have some Logitech software installed. There is a"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/faq.rst:99
msgid ""
"known bug/incompatibility in Logitech products. For example, if "
"lvprcsrv.exe is running, kill it and/or prevent it to start again at "
"reboot; it does not do anything really useful, not needed for operation "
"of web cameras or mice."
msgstr ""

